ywood, Montana", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017780901/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_juniper_ver01/data/sn85053305/00340581932/1923110201/0357.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_juniper_ver01:data:sn85053305:00340581932:1923110201:0356/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_juniper_ver01/data/sn85053305/00340581932/1923110201/0357.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85053305/1923-11-02/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_juniper_ver01/data/sn85053305/00340581932/1923110201/0357.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_juniper_ver01:data:sn85053305:00340581932:1923110201:0356/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_juniper_ver01/data/sn85053305/00340581932/1923110201/0357.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85053305/1923-11-02/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_juniper_ver01/data/sn85053305/00340581932/1923110201/0357.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85053305/1923-11-02/ed-1/?sp=2"], "batch": ["mthi_juniper_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/montana/", "2/united states/montana/sheridan/", "3/united states/montana/sheridan/plentywood/"], "contributor": ["montana historical society; helena, mt"], "date": "1923-11-02", "dates": ["1923-11-02"], "description": ["PRINCIPLE OF FREE SPEECH IN TWO CITIES AFTER HARD FIGHT AUTHORITIES IN NEW KENSINGTON PA AND BROCKTON MASS YIELD TO PUBLIC OPINION IN FREE SPEECH TESTS Two important victories in the na tionwide fight for freedom of speech at Brockton Mass and New Kensing ton Paare reported by the Amer ican Civil Liberties Union In both towns the efforts of local officials to suppress lawful gatherings of their citizens have been nullified through the pressure of public opinion and the intercession of the civil liberties body Retreating from his arbitrary posi tion of the last few months D Burns Burgess of New Kensington his issued a permit for a meeting of Italian workers at Garibaldi Hall on October 21 with Carlo Tresca the editor of the Italian monthly II Martello as principal speaker It will be the first such gathering to take place there in many months without police interfer ence The refusal of Mr Burns to grant permit for a similar meeting on September 30 makes the turn of af fairs the more significant A repre sentative of the Civil Liberties Union was to have spoken on the same plat form with Tresca at the time The official change"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-07-03T13:49:13.984Z", "group": ["ndnp/mthi", "montana-historical-society-helena-mt-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85053305/1923-11-02/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_juniper_ver01:data:sn85053305:00340581932:1923110201:0357/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=284&w=217", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_juniper_ver01:data:sn85053305:00340581932:1923110201:0357/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=568&w=435", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_juniper_ver01:data:sn85053305:00340581932:1923110201:0357/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1137&w=870", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/ser